  <brief_title>Trial of Afatinib in Pediatric Tumours</brief_title>
  <official_title>Phase I/II Open Label, Dose Escalation Trial to Determine the MTD, Safety, PK and Efficacy of Afatinib Monotherapy in Children Aged ≥1 Year to &lt;18 Years With Recurrent/Refractory Neuroectodermal Tumours, Rhabdomyosarcoma and/or Other Solid Tumours With Known ErbB Pathway Deregulation Regardless of Tumour Histology</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Boehringer Ingelheim</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Boehringer Ingelheim</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Open-label, dose escalation, monotherapy, basket trial with biomarker specific MTD expansion
      cohort/Phase II part.

      The trial will consist of 2 parts:

        1. Dose finding part to determine the MTD

        2. Biomarker specific MTD expansion cohort/Phase II part to assess clinical anti-tumour
           activity in included tumour types
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
